 of William the Conqueror at the Battle of Hastings. His memory was honoured by Normans and English alike, for his fairness and his piety. Edward's mother was Norman; he had spent part of his youth in Normandy; and William claimed to have been nominated by Edward as his successor. Edward was canonized in the 12th century, and came to be venerated throughout Europe as a model of a Christian king."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margeria de Bozon was born in North Brabant, Netherlands. She married Simon De Kirketon in 1127, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1105–Male":"1105–Surnud","1130–1155":"1130–1155","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","Sibthorpe, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Sibthorpe, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Noord-Brabant, Netherlands":"Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1105–Male":"1105–Kuollut","1130–1155":"1130–1155","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","Sibthorpe, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Sibthorpe, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Noord-Brabant, Netherlands":"Noord-Brabant, Alankomaat","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1105–Male":"1105–Décédé","1130–1155":"1130–1155","1155–Male":"1155–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","Sibthorpe, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Sibthorpe, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Noord-Brabant, Netherlands":"Brabant-septentrional, Pays-Bas","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Englan